<br>
1) Where they are.  If you can find the frozen river, you'll find most of the mammoths in the zone near its banks, on the island where the river forks, and (very) occasionally to the northeast by the ice giants.<br>
<br>
2) How they act.  Mammoths are not aggressive, but are social.  Big mammoths will help if you are attacking a mammoth calf, but the calfs will leave you alone.  They also have a HUGE hit radius, but it's possible to stick them on the pet if you pull with a spell and back up until it takes a swing at you.  That'll generally leave the pet between you and it, with you safely on the edge of the hit radius.  They occasionally double attack, and max for anywhere from 46 to 54.<br>
<br>
3) What they drop.  Rare is a mammoth rib bone, NODROP, LORE, used for the shaman totemic gloves quest.  Uncommon are the tusks, which weigh 10 pounds but sell for close to 10 plat.  Dimensional pockets are your friends.  Common is mammoth meat (undoubtedly used in some quest in Halas, but the barbarians distrust pretty much all of the mage races), and the occasional 24th level research component.<br>
<br>
4) What's around them.  In general, you'll be the baddest thing on the tundra by this level, but there are a few things to watch out for...<br>
    - There's a temple with a five icy orc spawn.  They're about levels 26-30 and stay put, but don't even think about trying to break it on your own.  Redwind, who spawns in the center, is a SK and has a component for ivy etched armor.  <br>
    - The tainted/corrupted mammoths are rare spawns.  The tainted hits for 60ish, and his death will cause the *immediate* spawn of the corrupted on the same spot.  The corrupted is aggressive, level 30, magic resistant, and hits for 65ish.  Be sure to pull your pet off of the tainted and kill it from a distance to avoid aggroing the corrupted.  The corrupted has a Chunk of Tundra, which is NODROP and is part of the druid epic.<br>
    - Martar Icebear is a barbarian, is level 32, doubles for 72, is magic resistant, and hates everybody.  He's takeable with a group, but deadly without one.  Uncommon loot is an ALL/ALL Cloak of the Icebear with +20 cold resist.  He also drops a kilt which is used for a wizard quest that I never read up on.  Best bet if he aggros you is to gate while your pet's still alive.<br>
    - Ice Giants are mid forties creatures.  There are three spawns of them outside of the entrance to Permafrost.  They don't wander and are nearly always camped by people who know what they're doing.  Woe betide the zone if one gets loose, though, because the guards can't kill them.  If you don't have your water focus by the time you're here, you can pick up the toes for nothing if you ask nicely.  This is also an opportunity to bank for people, if you're so inclined.<br>
    - Tundra Jack (a barbarian) and Iceberg (his FRICKIN' HUGE polar bear pal) run around a whole bunch in this zone.  Nothing to worry about if the barbarians don't aggro you, but I don't know how he reacts to dark elves and/or gnomes.  They're apparently tougher than the ice giants, according to the one person who actually fought them in the weeks I hunted there.<br>
     - Karg Icebear is probably the rarest and most sought after spawn in the zone.  He'll make cloaks for a polar bear skin and some plat; apparently you'll occasionally get Cloaks of the Icebear mixed in.  He also is part of an epic quest.  Topping things off, when killed (no idea of stats or level) he'll drop the Gigantic Zweihander.  You'll often get offered obscene amounts of money to hail him and keep him in one spot for someone else. :)<br>
     - Various snow orcs, snow leopards, and wooly spiders.  They're all green, but the snow orc shamen will sometimes aggro your pet, then run away at SoW speed (fun!).  They drop stackable items that are worth a few gold apiece.<br>
<br>
All in all, it's a great place for this spell level.  I'm only posting it now 'cause I've hit 34th and most of the mammoths are green.  I made it through 30 solo in about two evening's work.  I spent most of 29-31 and 32-34 here (brief stop in Iceclad), and made about 4500 plat in that time by binding in Qeynos (my hometown, so best prices), loading up on tusks until I couldn't run, and just gating to sell.<br>
<br>
